    • Constructor Detail

      • SamFileDataStoreBuilder

        public SamFileDataStoreBuilder(File samFile)
                        throws IOException
        Create a new Builder instance that will parse the given sam or bam encoded file. If there is an accompanying BAI file in the same directory named samFile.getName() + ".bai", then the index will be automatically detected and used by the Datastore to improve parsing runtime. If there is an index file but it does not follow the usual bam index conventions, then use indexFile(File) method to set the path to the index file.
        Parameters:
        samFile - the sam or bam file to use; can not be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file does not exist or is not readable.
        NullPointerException - if samFile is null.
        See Also:
        indexFile(File)

    • Method Detail

      • indexFile

        public SamFileDataStoreBuilder indexFile(File baiFile)
                                  throws IOException
        Set the non-standard path to the bam index file if there is one and it doesn't follow the usual bam file and naming convention of being in the same folder as the bam file and named bamFile.getName() + ".bai".
        Parameters:
        baiFile - the bai index file; can not be null, and must exist and be readable.
        Returns:
        this
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file does not exist or is not readable.
        NullPointerException - if baiFile is null.

      • validator

        public SamFileDataStoreBuilder validator(SamAttributeValidator validator)
        Set the SamAttributeValidator to use when parsing the sam or bam file. If this method is not called, then the default validator, ReservedAttributeValidator, is used.
        Parameters:
        validator - the validator to use; can not be null
        Returns:
        this
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if validator is null.
        See Also:
        ReservedAttributeValidator

      • filter

        public SamFileDataStoreBuilder filter(Predicate<SamRecord> filter)
        Add a filter that will exclude any SamRecords in the sam or bam file that do not pass the filter. If this method is called, then no filtering is performed, all records will be included in the datastore to be built.
        Parameters:
        filter - the filter used to exclude records, can not be null.
        Returns:
        this.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if filter is null.

      • build

        public SamFileDataStore build()
                       throws IOException
        Create a new SamFileDataStore using the configuration provided so far.
        Returns:
        a new SamFileDataStore; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the sam or bam file or the bai index file if there is one.
